22namespace webrtc {
23
24int GainController2::instance_count_ = 0;
25
26GainController2::GainController2()
27 : data_dumper_(rtc::AtomicOps::Increment(&instance_count_)),
28 gain_applier_(/*hard_clip_samples=*/false,
29 /*initial_gain_factor=*/0.0f),
30 limiter_(static_cast<size_t>(48000), &data_dumper_, "Agc2"),
31 calls_since_last_limiter_log_(0) {
32 if (config_.adaptive_digital.enabled) {
33 adaptive_agc_ =
34 std::make_unique<AdaptiveAgc>(&data_dumper_, config_.adaptive_digital);
35 }
36}
37
38GainController2::~GainController2() = default;
39
40void GainController2::Initialize(int sample_rate_hz, int num_channels) {
41 RTC_DCHECK(sample_rate_hz == AudioProcessing::kSampleRate8kHz ||
42 sample_rate_hz == AudioProcessing::kSampleRate16kHz ||
43 sample_rate_hz == AudioProcessing::kSampleRate32kHz ||
44 sample_rate_hz == AudioProcessing::kSampleRate48kHz);
45 limiter_.SetSampleRate(sample_rate_hz);
46 if (adaptive_agc_) {
47 adaptive_agc_->Initialize(sample_rate_hz, num_channels);
48 }
49 data_dumper_.InitiateNewSetOfRecordings();
50 data_dumper_.DumpRaw("sample_rate_hz", sample_rate_hz);
51 calls_since_last_limiter_log_ = 0;
52}
53
54void GainController2::Process(AudioBuffer* audio) {
55 data_dumper_.DumpRaw("agc2_notified_analog_level", analog_level_);
56 AudioFrameView<float> float_frame(audio->channels(), audio->num_channels(),
57 audio->num_frames());
58 // Apply fixed gain first, then the adaptive one.
59 gain_applier_.ApplyGain(float_frame);
60 if (adaptive_agc_) {
61 adaptive_agc_->Process(float_frame, limiter_.LastAudioLevel());
62 }
63 limiter_.Process(float_frame);
64
65 // Log limiter stats every 30 seconds.
66 ++calls_since_last_limiter_log_;
67 if (calls_since_last_limiter_log_ == 3000) {
68 calls_since_last_limiter_log_ = 0;
69 InterpolatedGainCurve::Stats stats = limiter_.GetGainCurveStats();
70 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AGC2 limiter stats"
71 << " | identity: " << stats.look_ups_identity_region
72 << " | knee: " << stats.look_ups_knee_region
73 << " | limiter: " << stats.look_ups_limiter_region
74 << " | saturation: " << stats.look_ups_saturation_region;
75 }
76}
77
78void GainController2::NotifyAnalogLevel(int level) {
79 if (analog_level_ != level && adaptive_agc_) {
80 adaptive_agc_->HandleInputGainChange();
81 }
82 analog_level_ = level;
83}
84
85void GainController2::ApplyConfig(
86 const AudioProcessing::Config::GainController2& config) {
87 RTC_DCHECK(Validate(config));
88
89 config_ = config;
90 if (config.fixed_digital.gain_db != config_.fixed_digital.gain_db) {
91 // Reset the limiter to quickly react on abrupt level changes caused by
92 // large changes of the fixed gain.
93 limiter_.Reset();
94 }
95 gain_applier_.SetGainFactor(DbToRatio(config_.fixed_digital.gain_db));
96 if (config_.adaptive_digital.enabled) {
97 adaptive_agc_ =
98 std::make_unique<AdaptiveAgc>(&data_dumper_, config_.adaptive_digital);
99 } else {
100 adaptive_agc_.reset();
101 }
102}
103
104bool GainController2::Validate(
105 const AudioProcessing::Config::GainController2& config) {
106 const auto& fixed = config.fixed_digital;
107 const auto& adaptive = config.adaptive_digital;
108 return fixed.gain_db >= 0.f && fixed.gain_db < 50.f &&
109 adaptive.vad_probability_attack > 0.f &&
110 adaptive.vad_probability_attack <= 1.f &&
111 adaptive.level_estimator_adjacent_speech_frames_threshold >= 1 &&
112 adaptive.initial_saturation_margin_db >= 0.f &&
113 adaptive.initial_saturation_margin_db <= 100.f &&
114 adaptive.extra_saturation_margin_db >= 0.f &&
115 adaptive.extra_saturation_margin_db <= 100.f &&
116 adaptive.gain_applier_adjacent_speech_frames_threshold >= 1 &&
117 adaptive.max_gain_change_db_per_second > 0.f &&
118 adaptive.max_output_noise_level_dbfs <= 0.f;
119}
